        <div class="doc-section">
          <h3 id="accessibility-guidelines" class="doc-h3">Accessibility Guidelines</h3>
          <table class="size-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Requirement</th><th>Implementation</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Alt Text</strong></td>
                <td>Use <code>alt="[User's full name]"</code> for image avatars so screen readers announce the person's identity.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Decorative Avatars</strong></td>
                <td>When avatar appears alongside a visible name, use <code>alt=""</code> or <code>aria-hidden="true"</code> to avoid redundant announcements.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Disabled State</strong></td>
                <td>Apply <code>aria-disabled="true"</code> to communicate the disabled state to assistive technologies.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Hover / Editable</strong></td>
                <td>Must be keyboard accessible. Use <code>aria-label="Change profile photo"</code> and ensure the overlay trigger is focusable.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Color Contrast</strong></td>
                <td>WCAG 2.1 AA (4.5:1) for initials text on tinted backgrounds. #0E2553 on #EAF0FC passes at 8.2:1.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Focus</strong></td>
                <td>Visible focus ring on editable avatars using <code>Border-Accent-Focus</code> token (#006AFF), 2px solid with 2px offset.</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>

